&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;County Durham and Darlington NHS Foundation Trust is one of the largest integrated care providers in England, serving a population of around 600,000 people. We are a high performing organization with a track record of success. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Radiology is a busy department providing Xray, CT, MRI, Fluoroscopy and Ultrasound services. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be required to carry out a variety of duties within the Radiology department and to assist radiographers, nurses and radiologists during procedures as required. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to be able to deal with telephone enquiries when necessary and to be able to prioritize your workload. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It is essential to have a good level of general education and basic understanding of IT. Good communication, interpersonal and organizational skills are also an essential requirement for this post. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous experience of working in a Radiology department is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note this position requires a DBS Disclosure Barring Services check &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
